Calculate the duty free quota and clear through customs the items you are bringing in above the quota. The app calculates the duty. You can pay directly in the app and go through the green channel.

 
If you want to bring in alcohol and tobacco products exceeding the duty free quota, you can use this app to calculate the duty you have to pay. Using this app you can clear up to 27 liters of beer or wine, four liters of spirits, 400 cigarettes, 500 grams of tobacco or snuff and 400 cigarette papers and tubes. You can also customs clear other goods than alcohol and tobacco, up to and including a value of NOK 20,000 per person.
 

When you have completed the customs clearance, a receipt will appear in the app. You may then cross the border through the green channel, and you do not have to present yourself to Customs.


You can choose to complete the customs clearance directly before crossing the border or clear your goods in advance.

At a customs control, you will be asked to show the receipt you have received. The receipt states what items you have cleared, and the time period in which you can cross the border.


You can choose to have a copy of the receipt sent to a given e-mail address. Note that the e-mail is not valid as receipt at a customs control.

You can choose to clear goods for one more person in addition to yourself. You must then cross the border together.

The app includes information on the duty free quota, the value limits, customs clearance and regulations concerning travelling to Norway.

RuterBillett requests access permission to the following functions: 

* Location/tracking:
Used in connection with ticket purchases so that RuterBillett can automatically suggest a ticket based on the zone in which you are located. You can still purchase a ticket even if the location function is turned off, but you must manually enter the stop or station from which the ticket will apply.

*Notifications:
A push notification is used during ticket transfer in order to update a ticket's status. You can still purchase a ticket even if the notification function is turned off.

*Background updates:
Used at night when updating your control code and today's picture so that next day you always have the valid code and picture ready for a ticket inspection. You can still purchase a ticket even if the background update function is turned off.

*Use of mobile data:
Used when communicating with Ruter's systems during ticket purchases. If the app's access to mobile data is blocked, you can only buy a ticket if you have access to a wireless network (Wi-Fi). You must also have network access in order to display the control code and today's picture during a ticket inspection.

If you want to block access, you can do so from your phone on RuterBillett's "Settings" page.

Appen finnes på norsk og engelsk.

Applikasjonen er utviklet av If Skadeforsikring.

With SJ’s app NORD, you can book train rides in Norway, from Bodø in the north to Oslo in the south, and in between. Use the app to purchase tickets, save you journey details and get an overview of your membership status with SJ Prio.

From June 2020, SJ runs seven train lines in Norway, and this app will be continuously developed and improved, in parallel to our web site and brand new travel services.

We’re looking forward to seeing you on board!

The mobile application makes it possible to buy single tickets and period tickets for all scheduled buses in Nordland. This applies to the scheduled buses set up under the auspices of the Nordland county municipality.

The validity of the ticket starts from the time it is purchased / activated. The ticket is valid for boarding (and transitions) until it expires on time.

As a traveler you are responsible for the validity of the ticket. Tickets must be purchased before boarding and must be presented when boarding and upon request. In cases where discounted tickets have been purchased, valid identification or documentation confirming this must be included throughout the journey. This must also be presented when boarding and upon request, together with a valid ticket.

Manage your adult Oyster and contactless cards on the move with the app.

• Top up pay as you go credit 
• Buy adult rate 7 Day, Monthly and Annual Travelcards, and Bus & Tram Passes
• View your Oyster card and contactless journey history
• Check contactless payments
• Check your pay as you go balance and see season tickets
• Check if you have any incomplete journeys
• Allow notifications when your pay as you go balance falls below a certain amount, or your Travelcard is about to expire

When you top up your credit or buy a Travelcard or Bus & Tram Pass, it will be available to collect after 30 minutes when you touch your Oyster card on a yellow card reader as part of a journey on any London bus, or at any Tube, DLR, London Overground, TfL Rail or National Rail station within the pay as you go area, tram stop or River Bus pier.
 
Keeping on top of your spend is easy; see the date, time and cost of your journeys from the last 8 weeks.
 
The TfL Oyster and contactless app will request access to your camera. This is so that you can scan your payment card. We will never store the scanned pictures. Alternatively you can enter the card details manually.
 
You can’t currently add Oyster photocards to this app.
You can’t currently buy discounted tickets through the app.
 
For security reasons the TfL Oyster and contactless app is not supported on jailbroken devices.

With the Bilkollektivet App you as a member of Bilkollektivet can easily reserve a car nearby when you need one.


With this App you get a quick overview of where there are available cars. You can easily reserve vehicles and manage your reservations.

BILKOLLEKTIVET

We are Norway's largest car sharing organization. As a non-profit member company, we aim to contribute to a greener city with fewer cars and less unnecessary driving.

Started in 1995 and operates as a co-op, with operations in Oslo and Stavanger. Members can also reserve vehicles with our collaborative partners in Trondheim and Bergen.

With the App you will have over 500 cars at your disposal only in Oslo.

Bilkollektivet buys, rents and leases a varying number of vehicles of different sizes to meet the needs of its members. During holidays and busy periods we increase our fleet to meet the increased demand.

Members can book directly in the app, use the cars 24 hours a day, and drive wherever they want throughout Europe.

Car sharing is for everyone! So, you are over 18 and have the patch you can join! As a member you also become a co-owner of the car fleet.


"It's easy to access a car. And it's affordable!"
